---
import { social } from "../data/portfolio";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import jeevanPhoto from "../assets/jeevan-photo.png";
---

<section id="about" class="reveal scroll-mt-24 border-b border-border py-16 sm:py-24">
  <div class="grid gap-12 sm:gap-16 sm:grid-cols-[0.8fr_1.5fr] items-start">
    
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold text-ink">About</h2>
      
      <div class="mt-8 relative aspect-[4/5] w-full max-w-xs mx-auto sm:mx-0 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-border shadow-md grayscale-[30%] hover:grayscale-0 transition-all duration-500">
        <Image 
          src={jeevanPhoto} 
          alt="Jeevan Kumar" 
          class="w-full h-full object-cover object-top"
          width={300}
          height={375}
        />
        <!-- Subtle noise overlay over the photo itself -->
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-amber-light mix-blend-overlay opacity-50 pointer-events-none"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-xl leading-8 text-ink/80 mt-2 sm:mt-4">
      <p>
        I've been writing code since 2020 — first as a founding engineer at a startup, then at a
        no-code AI platform, now mostly for myself.
      </p>
      <p>
        I grew up in Saharsa, Bihar, moved to Punjab for my studies, and somewhere along the way
        realized I'd rather build things I own than just things I'm paid to build. JaapMitra is
        the first one. More are coming.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of code — I'm training for a half marathon, slowly getting serious about it. I
        shoot on an iPhone 15 Pro Max and document whatever feels worth remembering on <a
          href={social.becomingjeevan}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-ink font-medium underline decoration-amber/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-amber transition-colors"
          >Becoming Jeevan</a
        > — a project about living intentionally, one chapter at a time.
      </p>
      <p>
        I like building things that feel complete. Apps that work offline. Products that don't
        need an account. Code that ships.
      </p>
    </div>
    
  </div>
</section>
